race.comment: INCANTATA (8) has been heavily bet her last three over this trip and don't discount the Tumut form. She will sit forward from an inside barrier and has won three times at the track. In good hands and this is winnable. GEOSTORM (3) is a threat. He's busting to win and last time led them up beaten 1L over a mile at Canberra in much stronger. The 3kg claim offsets some of the weight increase, and he has placed 2/3 here over this journey. FOCUS POINT (7) flopped in a CL2 at Braidwood as favourite but led all the way here prior over 1460m to win her Maiden. Has to skip across from a wide barrier but she has plenty of scope for improvement. BIG TIME CHARLIE (5) has been disappointing in 58s but gets a key jockey switch to Nick Heywood, who is building a strong record with the Pepper yard. They are persevering and he's been kept on the fresh side.
